text: Sunsari District is one of 14 districts in Koshi Province of Nepal. The district is in the eastern part of the Outer Terai. It covers an area of . According to the 2011 Nepal census, the population was 753,328. The district headquarters is at Inaruwa. == References == ==Other websites== * Official Web Portal of Sunsari District Category:Districts of Nepal
